But a nice value has no signification for us since we've only a realtime scheduler. If you look in the linux implementation you'll see that for SCHED_RR the nice value is only store and that nothing is done. The value is stored to be used if the scheduler is changed to an non realtime one later. For us it's not possible so I don't see what we can do???
